      • execute

        public void execute(com.raweng.built.BuiltExtensionCallback callback)
        Use the function to execute a plugin deployed on Built.io Backend Extension. .
        Parameters:
        callback - BuiltExtensionCallback object to notify the application when the request has completed.

        Example :
          // 'blt5d4sample2633b' is a dummy Application API key
  BuiltExtension extensionObject = Built.application(context, "blt5d4sample2633b").extension();

  extensionObject.setRequestMethod(BuiltExtension.RequestMethod.GET);

  //Send as it is url just without host.
  extensionObject.setRequestURL("/v1/app/config");

  WeakHashMap hashMap = new WeakHashMap<>();
   hashMap.put("device", "android");
   hashMap.put("version", "4.4.2");

  extensionObject.setRequestParameter(hashMap);

  extensionObject.execute(new BuiltExtensionCallback() {

      @Override
      public void onCompletion(BuiltResponseType responseType, Object object, BuiltError builtError) {

      }
  });

      • executeFunction

        public void executeFunction(com.raweng.built.BuiltExtensionCallback callback)
        Use the function to execute a extension deployed on Built.io Backend Extension. .
        Parameters:
        callback - BuiltExtensionCallback object to notify the application when the request has completed.

        Example :
          // 'blt5d4sample2633b' is a dummy Application API key
  BuiltExtension extensionObject = Built.application(context, "blt5d4sample2633b").extension("extension_key");

  extensionObject.setRequestMethod(BuiltExtension.RequestMethod.GET);

  extensionObject.setRequestURL("find");
                                OR
  extensionObject.setRequestURL("/find");

  extensionObject.executeFunction(new BuiltExtensionCallback() {

      @Override
      public void onCompletion(BuiltResponseType responseType, Object object, BuiltError builtError) {

      }
  });
